<p>You can use JSON with comments in it, if you load it as a text file, and then remove comments from it.</p>

<p>You can use <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/decomment">decomment</a> library for that. Below is a complete example.</p>

<p><strong>Input JSON (file input.js):</strong></p>

<pre><code>/*
* multi-line comments
**/
{
    "value": 123 // one-line comment
}
</code></pre>

<p><strong>Test Application:</strong></p>

<pre><code>var decomment = require('decomment');
var fs = require('fs');

fs.readFile('input.js', 'utf8', function (err, data) {
    if (err) {
        console.log(err);
    } else {
        var text = decomment(data); // removing comments
        var json = JSON.parse(text); // parsing JSON
        console.log(json);
    }
});
</code></pre>

<p>Output:</p>

<pre><code>{ value: 123 }
</code></pre>

<p>See also: <a href="https://github.com/vitaly-t/gulp-decomment">gulp-decomment</a>, <a href="https://github.com/vitaly-t/grunt-decomment">grunt-decomment</a></p>
